Via Dr. Iman:

Student teams from degree-granting institutions are invited to compete
in the annual SIGMOD programming contest. The winning team will be
awarded a prize of USD $5,000. One member of each of the top 5 teams...
will receive a travel grant to attend SIGMOD 2016 in San Francisco,
California.

The contest web site is now live at
http://dsg.uwaterloo.ca/sigmod16contest/

The contest description is available there now. Team registration
will open next week.

The SIGMOD'16 Programming Contest is brought to you by the Data
Systems Group at the University of Waterlo.

See more
ACM SIGMOD 2016 Programming Contest
Annual SIGMOD programming contest, open to students from degree-granting institutions.
dsg.uwaterloo.ca|By Data Systems Group, University of Waterloo
